igrams survive via the Greek Anthology, while most of his poems are transmitted by Athenaeus in his Deipnosophistai. The commentary is followed by an Auctarium Lectionum, an Appendix Coniecturarum, an Index verborum, an Index locorum, and an Index nominum et rerum notabilium. With its insights into literary Hellenistic epigram in an important phase of its development, this book represents an important tool for all those interested in epigram and Hellenistic literature in general.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Italian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aEpigrams, GreekxHistory and criticism. 0aGreek poetry, HellenisticxHistory and criticism. 4aAthenaeus. 4aGriechische Anthologie. 4aHedylus. 4aHellenistisches Epigramm. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAthenaeus.  aGreek Anthology.  aHedylus.  aHellenistic Epigram.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020z9783110704631oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831106309780 cprintz978311062962040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311063000840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110630008423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110630008/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020